{title: Howdy Neighbor Howdy}
{artist: Porter Wagoner}
{composer: Written by James Morris}

[G]Howdy neighbor howdy get [C]out and come right [G]in
We'll make a bowl of gravy to [D7]sop your biscuits [G]in
Boil a pot of coffee and [C]bake a big fat [G]hen
Cook another country ham to [D7]feed a hungry [G]man
[D7]Drive your wagon in the yard and [A7]turn your donkey [D7]loose
Kick that old hound out of the way and [A7]watch that fightin' [D7]goose
So [G]howdy neighbor howdy come [C]in and sit right [G]down
Come on and tell us all the news [D7]how are things in [G]town
We're so glad to see you been a [C]wonderin' how you've [G]been
Everybody's feelin' fine so [D7]let the fun [G]begin
[D7]Get the banjo off the wall and [A7]tune it up in [D7]A
Play some good ole country tunes like [A7]grandpa used to [D7]play
[G]Go and get your [D7]fiddle down play the [A7]tune that I like [D7]so
Somethin' bout an old man Clark I [A7]think his name was [D7]Joe
Repeat #1,2